I have gone three times now, and each has been fantastic. I usually hesitate to buy espresso for fear of disappointment, but today I caved and it sealed my appreciation for this place! The BLT Benedict and potatoes are delicious, the pancakes fluffy and so tasty, my latte was great, and the horchata is also interesting and flavorful. Also, it’s worth noting that the prices are not inflated compared to other spots- we will continue to frequent Breakfast House!

A delightful place to enjoy breakfast and brunch. What first attracted me to this relatively new spot two blocks from home is the friendliness of the staff. That brings me to the food…I’m a waffle nut and truly appreciate how they make theirs so tasty; the omelets are large and so delicious {I relish the Paris Omelet}, for a brunch they serve several items which go beyond the bacon & eggs.  Their croissant sandwich is really tasty. Last but not least the chicken lunch or chicken on a waffle is outstanding. They also have outdoor seating. I always enjoy eating at the BREAKFAST HOUSE.

The chicken and waffles were great. The chicken itself was perfectly flavorful, crisp, and cooked to perfection. The honey mustard that came with it was whatever and the syrup was also pretty good. Didn't have the same consistency as most real Maple syrups but it was still enjoyable.  The "chorizo" hash really didn't have enough chorizo. That's I think the biggest complaint for my experience. It came out and I actually thought they brought me the wrong order. It wasn't until I flipped the eggs over and discovered roughly a quarter cup of overcooked chorizo. It really should have been corn, potatoes, and eggs with a side of guacamole and chorizo. If you ask me I'd get rid of the sauce and maybe even the corn and double up on chorizo. Heck, I think there might have been more guacamole than chorizo.  I was also surprised they served Intelligentsia Coffee. Kudos!  The staff were very nice and accommodating. I think that definitely helps the experience!  3/5 for good 5/5 for service/staff 4/5 overall
